label.value: decreased growth on myristic acid carbon source

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the decrease in growth of individuals or populations relative to normal in a medium containing myristic acid as the carbon source.

label.value: effector-mediated suppression of host PAMP-triggered immunity present

definition.value: A cell signaling pathway phenotype where the molecular pattern-induced host innate immune response signaling pathway is suppressed by a pathogen. (GO:0052034)

label.value: stunted host growth during pathogen colonization

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the presence of a pathogen (or symbiont) has resulted in a decreased size of the host organism.

label.value: increased number of host side shoots during pathogen colonization

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the presence of a pathogen (or symbiont) has resulted in an increased number of side shoots produced by the host organism.

label.value: increased size of pathogen vacuoles during host colonization

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the size of the pathogen vacuoles are larger than normal during host colonization. This relates to the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.

label.value: increased cellular melanin accumulation

definition.value: A single species individual organism phenotype where the accumulation of melanin in a cell is increased.

label.value: sensitive to potassium chloride

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to potassium chloride. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.

label.value: sensitive to sorbitol

definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to sorbitol. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.

label.value: abolished development of asexual reproductive structure

definition.value: A single species phenotype where the asexual reproductive developmental process whose specific outcome is the progression of structures that will be used in the process of creating new individuals, from their formation to the mature structures is abolished (it was present and is now absent) (GO:0048608).

label.value: increased number of hyphal septa

definition.value: An individual organism cellular process phenotype in which the number of septa produced during hyphae formation is increased.

This phenotype is related to division rather than growth and usually indicates that hyphae with more septa have an increased number of smaller individual cells. If experiments also indicate an increase or reduction in hyphal growth please coannotate in the hyphal growth branch.

label.value: decreased number of asexual reproductive structures

definition.value: A single species phenotype where the frequency of occurrence of asexual reproductive structures is decreased.

label.value: decreased number of septum in asexual spore

definition.value: A single species phenotype where the frequency of occurrence of septum within an asexual spore is decreased.

label.value: host PAMP-triggered immunity signaling activated by pathogen present

definition.value: A cell signaling pathway phenotype where the host pattern recognition receptor signaling pathway is directly induced by a pathogen. This can include any series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a pattern recognition receptor (PRR) binding to a pathogen-derived physiological ligand. PRR ligands are usually referred to as pathogen-associated molecular pattern (PAMPs) or microbe-associated molecular pattern (MAMPs), structures conserved among microbial species (GO:0002221).

label.value: normal pathogen protein localization to host chloroplast

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the localization of a pathogen protein to the host chloroplast is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished pathogen protein localization to host chloroplast

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype in which the localization of a pathogen protein to the host chloroplast is abolished (i.e.the protein was localized to the host chloroplast and now is not).

label.value: decreased level of host defense-related RNA involved in a pathogen interaction

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host defense-related RNA usually present during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: effector-mediated suppression of host effector triggered immunity present

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion initially induced by the host activating its own hypersensitive response in defense, is subsequently suppressed by a pathogen effector.

label.value: cellular metabolic process phenotype

definition.value: A single organism phenotype that affects the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances. (GO:0044237)

label.value: unaltered reactive oxygen species production

definition.value: A single species metabolic cellular process phenotype in which the formation of reactive oxygen species (any molecules or ions formed by the incomplete one-electron reduction of oxygen) is unaltered.(GO:1903409)

label.value: decreased reactive oxygen species production

definition.value: A single species metabolic cellular process phenotype in which the formation of reactive oxygen species (any molecules or ions formed by the incomplete one-electron reduction of oxygen) is decreased.(GO:1903409)

label.value: abnormal spatial extent of reactive oxygen species production

definition.value: A single species localization phenotype in which ROS are produced over a different portion of the cell than normal.

label.value: normal host size during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A host morphology phenotype where the size of the host is normal (indistinguishable from wild type) during pathogen invasion.

label.value: increased host membrane blebbing during pathogen invasion

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the morphology of the host plasma membrane has increased blebbing during pathogen invasion.

label.value: hyphal hyper branching

definition.value: A single species cell morphology phenotype in which fungal hyphae form an increased number of branches.

label.value: decreased pathogen chitin fragment binding

definition.value: A single species pathogen molecular function phenotype in which pathogen chitin fragment binding by a pathogen gene product is decreased.

label.value: decreased level of pathogen reactive oxygen species production within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of pathogen produced reactive oxygen species (ROS) usually present during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: increased level of pathogen reactive oxygen species production within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of pathogen produced reactive oxygen species (ROS) usually present during infection is higher than normal.

label.value: pathogen tissue to tissue migration within host phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype which affects the directional tissue to tissue movement of the pathogen within the host organism (GO:0044001).

label.value: abolished pathogen tissue to tissue migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the ability of the pathogen to move directionally from tissue to tissue within the host organism is abolished (pathogen migration was present within the host and is now absent).

label.value: host defense-induced phenolic compound absent

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the host phenolic compounds usually present during infection are absent or at a level too low to detect.
decreased level of CHEBI:33853 in host during GO:051702 interaction with symbiont

label.value: abnormal host seed development induced by pathogen

definition.value: A host reproductive phenotype with pathogen where the process of host seed development is abnormal (GO:0048316).

label.value: absence of host seed development induced by pathogen

definition.value: A host reproductive phenotype with pathogen where the process of host seed development is absent (GO:0048316).

label.value: pathogen modulation of host immune system process phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype that affects a host immune system process during pathogen infection (GO:0002376).

This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: presence of pathogen inhibition of host immune response protease

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the host immune response protease activity is inhibited by the pathogen.

label.value: pathogen modulation of host process phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which a pathogen effects a change in the structure or processes of its host organism (GO:0044003).

label.value: decreased level of host defense-induced RNA

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host RNA usually present during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: normal pathogen protein localization within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the localization of a pathogen protein in a host cell is normal.

label.value: effector-mediated immune suppression phenotype

definition.value: A phenotype dependent on an interaction between a pathogen effector and a host process in order for the pathogen to suppress the host immune system. An effector is an entity derived from a pathogenic or non-pathogenic species that either activates or suppresses host defenses or other host responses.

label.value: infective ability phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype that affects the infective ability of a pathogen during attempted colonization of a host.
For use in the annotation extension infective ability.

label.value: absence of effector-independent host hypersensitive response

definition.value: A single species phenotype where the immune system process of host tissue hypersensitive response is absent in a pathogen effector-independant manner. (i.e. an alteration within the host does not activate the hypersensitive response in the absence of a pathogen).

label.value: normal level of deoxynivalenol

definition.value: A single species cell phenotype in which the amount of deoxynivalenol measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: presence of melanin accumulation in pathogen asexual spore within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction, in which the accumulation of melanin within a pathogen asexual spore, usually present during infection, is present.

label.value: decreased level of host defense-induced reactive oxygen species

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host produced reactive oxygen species (ROS), often associated with an oxidative burst response  during infection is lower than normal.

label.value: increased level of host defense-induced reactive oxygen species

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, in which the level of host produced reactive oxygen species (ROS), often associated with an oxidative burst response  during infection is higher than normal.

label.value: inhibition of pathogen chorismate mutase by host absent

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction molecular function phenotype in which host-mediated inhibition of a pathogen chorismate mutase is absent.

label.value: inhibition of pathogen chorismate mutase by host present

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction molecular function phenotype in which host-mediated inhibition of a pathogen chorismate mutase is present.

label.value: host defense-induced substance level phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, which affects the level of a host produced substance during infection.

label.value: level of pathogen produced substance within host phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype, which affects the level of a pathogen produced substance during host infection.

label.value: outcome of interaction phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype that affects the disease outcome of a pathogen host interaction.
For use in the annotation extension outcome of interaction.

label.value: disease absent

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where disease is absent.
